# Finance Buddy — Missing Parts to Add

Areas not yet covered in the Project Description, Notes, or Improvement Suggestions documents.

---

## 1. Monetization / Business Model

No document discusses how Finance Buddy generates revenue.

**Options to consider:**
- **Freemium tiers:** Free education and budgeting; paid access to advanced AI insights, deeper analytics, or unlimited chat
- **Subscription model:** Monthly or annual plans with tiered feature access
- **Affiliate revenue:** Partnerships with brokers or financial products (disclosed transparently)
- **Premium AI features:** Deeper portfolio analysis, priority response times, extended conversation history
- **No ads policy:** Explicitly commit to an ad-free experience — trust is core to the product and ads undermine it

---

## 2. Competitive Landscape

No competitive analysis exists. Finance Buddy needs clear positioning against existing players.

**Investing apps:** Robinhood, Acorns, Stash
- These focus on execution, not education. Finance Buddy leads with learning.

**Budgeting apps:** Mint, YNAB
- These track money but don't teach investing or offer AI guidance.

**AI finance bots:** Cleo, Plum
- These automate savings but lack portfolio simulation, structured education, or explainable recommendations.

**Finance Buddy's differentiator:**
- All-in-one (education + budgeting + investing guidance) with AI as the core engine, not a bolt-on feature.

