## 6. AI Model Strategy & Cost Management

The technical architecture references "LLM" but doesn't address model selection or cost control.

**Decisions to make:**
- **Model selection:** Which LLM(s) and why — balance cost, quality, and latency
- **Token budget:** Per-user usage caps or throttling to control API spend
- **Response caching:** Cache common Q&A responses (e.g., "What is a P/E ratio?") to reduce redundant API calls
- **Architecture approach:** Fine-tuning vs. prompt engineering vs. retrieval-augmented generation (RAG)
- **Latency targets:** Define acceptable response times for chat (e.g., under 2 seconds)
- **Fallback models:** Use a smaller/cheaper model for simple queries, reserve the primary model for complex ones

